  "prompt": "Why can't Borussia Dortmund keep hold of their key players?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why Borussia Dortmund struggles to retain their top players:\n\n1. Financial limitations\n- They cannot compete financially with larger clubs like Bayern Munich, Real Madrid, and other wealthy European teams\n- Lower wage budget compared to top clubs\n- Unable to offer comparable salaries to retain star players\n\n2. Club business model\n- Dortmund is known for developing young talent and selling players at high prices\n- They use transfer fees to financially sustain the club and reinvest in new young prospects\n\n3. Sporting ambitions of players\n- Top players often want to win major trophies like the Champions League\n- Dortmund, while competitive, hasn't consistently been at the highest European level\n- Players seek opportunities at clubs with more consistent Champions League success\n\n4. Competitive transfer market\n- Big clubs are always interested in Dortmund's talented players\n- Release clauses and attractive transfer offers make it difficult to retain players\n\n5. Club's strategic approach\n- Dortmund sees player development and sales as a key part of their long-term strategy\n- They accept that top talents will likely move on after reaching a certain level\n\nPlayers like Robert Lewandowski, Ousmane Demb\u00e9l\u00e9, Jadon Sancho, and Erling Haaland have all left the club for these reasons.",
